body:
Hello,

I have found a bug with the Flutter plugin when a new plugin is created.
The content of the src/main folder of the Android seems empty with the Project view.
The files are on the filesystem, but invisible in IntelliJ : https://imgur.com/a/NZrj2jg

## Steps to reproduce

1. File -> New Project
2. Select Flutter
3. Choose a "Plugin" project type
4. Click on Finish

@stevemessick, I believe this is what you were seeing in AS 3.2?
@devoncarew When I looked into it I thought the details were so different it was not related to that. However, I am hopeful that #2504 will fix this problem.
Given that, should we consider that PR for the release?
@stevemessick: now that #2504 has landed can we treat this as fixed?
This problem isn't fixed. I'm just hoping whatever broke in AS is fixed by the stable release. It IS fixed in canary.

Ah!  Thanks for the context.  Is it worth documenting as a "known issue"?

https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij#known-issues
I believe this was fixed a/o RC3, and stayed fixed in 3.2 stable. Please reopen if you find otherwise.
